commit_message:
Only returns chromosome names that have an entry.

This had changed in cyvcf2 0.8.3.
Assuming we only use this for small VCF files (famous last words).
Use SOAP with suds for variant call.
Update license string as also done for conda.
Update for new location and packaging.

Merge branch 'fix-issue-2' into 'master'

Ignore deleted alleles.

See merge request PharmacogenomicsPipe/variant_tools!5

Ignore deleted alleles.

Delete alleles - represented by '*' - must be preceded by a deletion.
This deletion already encapsulates the sequence change.

cyvcf2's `seqnames` attribute only returns the chromosomes in the vcf
index file when the VCF is compressed and indexed.

This means that whenever there are no variants on a particular
chromosome, that chromosome will not be present in the accession_dict,
even though the chromosome _is_ defined in the VCF header.

This is a workaround so that we don't issue a KeyError.
